---
// This page a_cts as a redirect to the default locale.
// Astro's i18n routing with `prefixDefaultLocale: true` should handle this,
// but having a root index.astro helps the build process identify the root.
// We can explicitly redirect if needed, or let Astro's default behavior manage it.

// Option 1: Let Astro's default i18n routing handle it (often works if the file just exists)
// No specific code needed in many cases, just the presence of this file.

// Option 2: Explicit redirect (more robust if Astro doesn't auto-redirect)
// import { Astro } from 'astro';
// const defaultLocale = Astro.config.i18n.defaultLocale;
// return Astro.redirect(`/${defaultLocale}/`);

// For now, creating a minimal page content. Astro should still redirect.
// If not, explicit redirect will be added.
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0;url=/en/">
  <title>Redirecting...</title>
  <link rel="canonical" href="/en/" />
</head>
<body>
  <p>If you are not redirected automatically, follow this <a href='/en/'>link to the English homepage</a>.</p>
</body>
</html>
<style>
  body { font-family: sans-serif; text-align: center; padding-top: 50px; }
</style>
